@@TJvCustomListBox.Alignment
Summary
  Determines how the text is aligned within the list box control.
Description
  Use Alignment to change the way the text is aligned within the listbox control. These are the possible
  values:

  <TABLE>
  Value           Meaning
  -----           -------
  taLeftJustify   Align text on the left side in the edit control.
  taCenter        Center the text in the edit control.
  taRightJustify  Align text on the right side in the edit control.
  </TABLE>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.Count
Summary
  Indicates the number of items in the list box.
Description
  Use Count to determine the number of items in the list box. You can only set Count when the Style 
  property is lbVirtual or lbVirtualOwnerDraw, or OwnerData is set to True, in which case you must set
  this property.
See Also
  OwnerData
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.DeleteAllButSelected
Summary
  Deletes all strings that are not selected from the list box.
Description
  Call DeleteAllButSelected to delete all strings, that are not selected from the list box.
Note
  MultiSelect must be set to True.
See Also
  DeleteAllButSelected, DeleteSelected, InvertSelection, SelectAll, UnselectAll
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.DeleteExactString
Summary
  Deletes specific strings from the list box.
Description
  Call DeleteExactString to remove strings from the list box that are equal to Value. 
Parameters
  Value         - The string value to be removed from the list box.
  All           - Specifies whether to delete all strings that match Value.
  CaseSensitive - Specifies whether the strings in the list box must be compared case-sensitive with
                  Value.
See Also
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.DeleteSelected
Summary
  Deletes the selected items from the list box
Description
  Call DeleteSelected to delete the selected items from the list box.
See Also
  DeleteAllButSelected, DeleteSelected, InvertSelection, SelectAll, UnselectAll
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.HintColor
Summary
  Determines the color of the hint boxes for the Help Hints for the list box.
Description
  Use HintColor to specify the hint box color. A default color value of clInfoBk is set for the
  HintColor property in the constructor when the application is created. To change the HintColor
  assign it a new TColor value.
See Also
  HotTrack
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.HorzExtent
Summary
  Specifies the horizontally scrollable width of the list box, in pixels. 
Description
  Use HorzExtent to specify the number of pixels by which the list box can be scrolled horizontally.
  If the actual width of the list box is smaller than HorzExtent, and ScrollBars equals ssHorizontal or
  ssBoth, the list box displays the horizontal scroll bar. If the actual width of the list box is equal
  to or greater than HorzExtent, the horizontal scroll bar is hidden. 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.HotTrack
Summary
  Specifies whether the list box is highlighted when the mouse passes over it.
Description
  Set HotTrack to True to provide visual feedback about which item is under the mouse; the font 
  specified by HotTrackFont is used for the list box text. When HotTrack is False, there is no visual 
  feedback when the mouse passes over the list box.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.InvertSelection
Summary
  Invert item selection.
Description
  If the MultiSelect property is True, InvertSelection selects all items that are current deselected, 
  and deselects all items that are currently selected.

  If the MultiSelect property is False, InvertSelection does nothing.
See Also
  DeleteAllButSelected, DeleteSelected, InvertSelection, SelectAll, UnselectAll
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.MoveSelectedDown
Summary
  Moves the selected strings one position down in the list box.
Description
  Use the MoveSelectedDown method to move all selected strings one position down in the list box. If
  the last item in the list box is selected then no items are moved.
See Also
  MoveSelectedUp
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.MoveSelectedUp
Summary
  Moves the selected strings one position up in the list box.
Description
  Use the MoveSelectedDown method to move all selected strings one position up in the list box. If
  the first item in the list box is selected then no items are moved.
See Also
  MoveSelectedDown
