Summary
  Occurs when a string in the list box is deleted.
Description
  Write an OnDeleteString event handler to respond when a string is deleted from the list box.
Parameters
  Sender - The object that triggered the event.
  Item   - Indicates the string that has been deleted.
See Also
  OnAddString, OnChange
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.OnGetText
<COMBINEWITH TJvListBoxDataEvent>
Summary
  Occurs immediately before a string is displayed in the list box.
Description
  Use OnGetText to dynamically supply the items in the list box. Set Text to a string value that must
  be displayed at position Index in the list box.

  OnGetText occurs only if OwnerData is True.
Parameters
  Sender - The object that triggered the event.
  Index  - The index of the desired item.
  Text   - Determines the string that is displayed at position Index in the list box.
See Also
  OwnerData
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.OnHorizontalScroll
<COMBINEWITH TJvScrollEvent>
Summary
  Occurs when the user scrolls the horizontal scroll bar with the mouse or keyboard.
Description
  Write an OnHorizontalScroll event handler to respont when the user scrolls the horizontal scroll bar.
  Set dontScroll to False to prevent the list box's horizontal scroll bar to scroll in response of this
  event. Set dontScroll to True to allow the list box's horizontal scroll bar to scroll in response of
  this event.
  
  Use Msg to determine whether to set dontScroll to True or False.
Parameters
  sender     - The object that triggered the event.
  Msg        - Represents the parameters of the Windows message.
  dontScroll - Determines whether the list box will respond on the scroll event, and adjust the 
               horizontal scroll bar.
See Also
  OnVerticalScroll
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.OnMouseEnter
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves over the list box.
Description
  Write an OnMouseEnter event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse over the 
  list box.
See Also
  HotTrack, OnMouseLeave
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.OnMouseLeave
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves off the list box.
Description
  Write an OnMouseLeave event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse off the
  list box. For example, you can use this event to undo changes that were made in an OnMouseEnter
  event handler.
See Also
  HotTrack, OnMouseEnter
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.OnParentColorChange
Summary
  Occurs when the color property for the parent of the list box changes.
Description
  Write an OnParentColorChange event to take specific action when the ParentColor property changes.
See Also
