@@TJvCustomListBox.OwnerData
Summary
  Specifies whether the list box control is virtual.
Description
  Set OwnerData to True to specify that the list box is virtual. A virtual list box can contain a 
  huge number of strings. Specifically, in Windows 95, 98 and Me the maximum number is 32,767; In 
  Windows 2000 and XP the maximum number is 2,147,483,647. However, you must manage the items of a virtual
  list box using the OnGetText event handler. 
  
  When creating a virtual list box, you must set the Count property to the number of items in the virtual
  list.

  The only information contained in a virtual list box control is the selection and focus information.
  No object can be associated with a string in a virtual list box.
See Also
  Count, OnGetText
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.ScrollBars
Summary
  Determines whether the list box control has scroll bars.
Description
  Use ScrollBars to give a list box control horizontal or vertical scroll bars. ScrollBars can take 
  one of the following values:
  <TABLE>
  Value	         Meaning
  -----          -------
  ssNone         The control has no scroll bars.
  ssHorizontal   The control has a single scroll bar on the bottom edge.
  ssVertical     The control has a single scroll bar on the right edge.
  ssBoth         The control has a scroll bar on both the bottom and right edges.
  </TABLE>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.SearchExactString
Summary
  Returns the position of a string in the list.
Description
  Call SearchExactString to obtain the position of the first occurrence of a string that matches Value.
  A string matches Value if it is identical to Value or, if CaseSensitive is False, if it differs only in
  case. 
Parameters
  Value         - The string to search for.
  CaseSensitive - Indicates whether the match must be case-sensitive.
See Also
  SearchPrefix, SearchSubString
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.SearchPrefix
Summary
  Returns the position of a string in the list.
Description
  Call SearchPrefix to obtain the position of the first occurrence of a string that has a prefix that
  matches Value. A prefix matches Value if it is identical to Value or, if CaseSensitive is False, if
  it differs only in case. 
Parameters
  Value         - The prefix to search for.
  CaseSensitive - Indicates whether the match must be case-sensitive.
See Also
  SearchExactString, SearchSubString
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.SearchSubString
Summary
  Returns the position of a string in the list.
Description
  Call SearchSubString to obtain the position of the first occurrence of a string that has a substring
  that matches Value. A substring matches Value if it is identical to Value or, if CaseSensitive is 
  False, if it differs only in case. 
Parameters
  Value         - The substring to search for.
  CaseSensitive - Indicates whether the match must be case-sensitive.
See Also
  SearchExactString, SearchPrefix
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.SelectAll
Summary
  Selects all items in the list box.
Description
  Use SelectAll to select all items in the list box.
See Also
  DeleteAllButSelected, DeleteSelected, InvertSelection, UnselectAll
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.Sorted
Summary
  Specifies whether the items in a list box are arranged alphabetically.
Description
  Use Sorted to sort the items by setting its value to True. If Sorted is False, the items are unsorted. 
  When Sorted is True, items are automatically added or inserted into the list box in alphabetical order.
Note
  Sorted raises an exception when set to True and OwnerData is True; Sorted has no effect if Listbox's 
  style is lbVirtual or lbVirtualOwnerDraw
See Also
  OwnerData
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.UnselectAll
Summary
  Deselects all items in the list box.
Description
  Use UnselectAll to deselect all items in the list box.
See Also
  DeleteAllButSelected, DeleteSelected, InvertSelection, SelectAll
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.UpdateCount
Summary
  Updates the list box's item count.
Description
  UpdateCount is called automatically when the list box's item count is changed. Call UpdateCount to
  explicitly set the list box's item count.
See Also
  Count, OnGetText
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomListBox.UpdateHorzExtent
Summary
  Updates the horizontally scrollable width of the list box.
Description
  UpdateHorzExtent is called automatically when the list box's horizontally scrollable width is changed.
  Call UpdateHorzExtent to explicitly set the list box's horizontally scrollable width.
See Also
  HorzExtent
